Disabled regression test for issue #580: numeric literals are not checked for overflow.

Currently the compiler accepts an out-of-range integer literal like `999999999999999999` for a value of type `int` and silently emits invalid IL (`ldc.i4 999999999999999999`) which then causes ilasm to fail with an opaque syntax error. Expected behaviour is a clear compile-time diagnostic at the literal naming the offending value and the target type.

Re-enable by deleting this `disabled` file once the compiler reports overflow at parse or semantic time.
